To compare the observations from real data with a known truth set, we developed LRTK-SIM, a simulator that follows the workflow of the 10x Chromium system and generates synthetic Linked-Reads like those produced by an Illumina HiSeqX machine (Supplementary Information and Fig. S9). Based on the parameters commonly used by 10x Genomics Linked-Read sequencing and the characteristics of our libraries, LRTK-SIM generated simulated data sets from the human reference (hg38), explicitly modeling the 5 key steps in real data generation. Parameters in parentheses are from the standard 10x Genomics protocol: (i) shearing genomic DNA into long fragments (W\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
